2026-04-21 02:41:31 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1', 'Control module 2', 'Control module 3', 'Control module 4', 'Control module 5', 'Control module 6', 'Control module 7', 'Control module 8'] hypothesis_explanation='The lack of any control module switch indicator LEDs being visibly present and the fact that both Control Module 1 and 2 specifically do not have their respective LEDs present (and cannot be replaced) suggest that all the control modules are missing their switch LEDs. As these LEDs (and their series resistors) must be present for the parallel paths to be complete for current flow through to the lamp, their absence creates open circuits at each module, preventing current from reaching the load and none of the control indicators or the lamp lights up. The root cause is the physical absence of essential LED indicator components in each control module, resulting in open-circuit conditions throughout the chain.'
